=== DWA-X1850 A1 (2001:3321) on Raspberry Pi 5 -- morrownr rtw89_8852au_git ===
Date: Sun Apr 12 2026
Kernel: 6.12.47+rpt-rpi-2712 (Pi OS stock kernel)
Host: Raspberry Pi 5 (aarch64)
USB controller: Broadcom RP1 xHCI
Interface: wlan1 (wlan0 is built-in brcmfmac)

IMPORTANT CONTEXT:
Pi OS stock kernel 6.12 has ZERO rtw89 USB modules. No rtw89_usb.ko,
no rtw89_8852au.ko, no rtw89_8852bu.ko, no rtw89_8922au.ko. Out-of-tree
morrownr/rtw89 DKMS is the ONLY way Pi OS users can use these adapters.
This makes Bitterblue's switch-mode fix doubly important for Pi users:
not only does it enable USB 3.0 SuperSpeed, it's part of the package
they NEED just to have working hardware at all.

USB ENUMERATION:
  Bus 4 Port 1, speed 5000 Mbps (USB 3.0 SuperSpeed)
  Switch-mode SUCCESSFUL on aarch64 + Broadcom RP1 xHCI

WIFI LINK:
  SSID: 8 Hertz WAN IP, 5 GHz (5500 MHz)
  BSSID: 00:00:00:00:00:A2 (forced via nmcli)
  Signal: -36 dBm
  rx bitrate: 1134.2 Mbit/s, tx bitrate: 1200.9 Mbit/s (identical to Framework)

IPERF3 UPLOAD (30s): 682 Mbit/sec, 2.38 GB, 0 retransmits
IPERF3 DOWNLOAD (30s): 609 Mbit/sec, 2.13 GB

SIGNIFICANCE:
  Fix works cross-architecture (aarch64 vs x86_64) and cross-controller
  (Broadcom RP1 vs Intel Tiger Lake xHCI). Upload slightly lower than
  Framework (682 vs 802 Mbps, likely CPU factor), download higher
  (609 vs 425 Mbps). Both well above USB 2.0 ceiling.
